The White House has announced the full program and talent line-up for the 2016 Easter Egg Roll, which is in its 138th year and is the largest annual public event at the White House. The event will take place on March 28th and will feature live music, sports courts, cooking stations, storytelling, and Easter egg rolling. First Lady Michelle Obama will also participate in the first-ever White House Fun Run to promote active and healthy lifestyles for kids. The event will include performances by Tony Award-winning artist Idina Menzel, as well as other artists like Silento, Daya, Echosmith, and Sesame Street. The event will also include healthy eating demonstrations, sports activities, and interactive dance parties. Tickets for the event were distributed through an online lottery system, with over 35,000 people receiving tickets.